    <!-- API Key Security -->
    <string name="api_key_security_title">API Key Security Information</string>    <string name="api_key_security_explanation">
        Your API Key is stored securely.\n
        Your OpenAI API key is encrypted and stored securely on your device using Android\'s EncryptedSharedPreferences. This encryption uses the Android KeyStore system for maximum security.\n\n
        Client-side only architecture:\n
        All API requests are made directly from your device to OpenAI. Your API key is never sent to our servers or stored elsewhere.\n\n
        Complete transparency:\n
        You can view exactly how your API key is handled in our open-source code at https://github.com/Tomer-Barak/PostMuse. The app code shows that API requests go directly to OpenAI\'s servers with your key.\n\n
        API key usage:\n
        Your key is only used for:\n
        - Text generation with OpenAI\'s API\n
        - Image analysis with Vision API\n\n
        Your data stays private:\n
        Since we don\'t route your API requests through our servers, we never see your data or API key.
    </string>
